    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted because the COU is explicitly bounded to the single ASTM F1717 fixture configuration tested, and the normalized error metric E/uval < 1.96 for all QoIs confirms adequate predictive accuracy within that scope. Overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support a Medium assurance level conclusion for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw compression-bending FEA model.",
